Once again, in the Star Trek franchise we find a fantasying about technologies, abilities and other facets of a supposed space-faring civilization that are unreasonable, unrealistic and extremely unlikely.<br>
A good science fiction book or movie will feature in it a future mental or visual pictorial description that we the viewers or readers can readily connect to and appreciate as being plausible (ex. The films 2001: A Space Odyssey and Gattaca)<br>
Star Trek and Star Wars inspire couch potatoes not Werner von Braun’s.   <br>
